6:
Ugh, no luck here either. This place
is, like, a total ghost town.
13:
Nada. Zippo. Zilch. Just like Grandpa
said. That's totally weird, right?
16:
Y-you don't think... that Devourer of
Stars thing... woke up, do you?
19:
L-let's not think about that! In any
case, it doesn't seem to be related
to the World Flipper.
22: Still, the mermaids are worried, right?
24:
Well, it's probably best to check
anywa—
35: Amelia, get Stella out of here!
51: He's alive... But what is he doing here?
55:
Well, it matters not. I have no
responsibility to save this boy...
60:
Curses! Why does this only ever
happen to me?!
66:
Awake at last, I see. I thought you
might not return to the land of the
living.
70:
I am Malviola. As your savior, I
expect your gratitude.
74:
Even if it WAS my fault you almost
died...
81:
How was I supposed to know a
human would be roaming around?
84:
The familiars I deployed to clear out
the area mistook you for a target
and attacked. Surely that is not MY
fault.
86:
Besides, who ARE you exactly? How
are you able to survive at the
bottom of the ocean? What power is
allowing you to do such things?
88:
Were you investigating the northern
waters? I'm sorry, I cannot let you—
93:
Whoa, whoa, whoa! Slow down! This
is a lot to take in at once!
97:
Well, what am I supposed to do
about that? It's been a long time
since I spoke with a human.
102: Now... May I continue my questions?
110:
Well, this is great. Just GREAT. I had
no idea I'd intruded upon mermaid
territory...
112:
Your name is Alk, correct? I
apologize, but I cannot allow you to
return to your friends just yet.
115:
Go ahead, open that door over there
and tell me what you see.
122:
Correct. The bottom, to be precise. I
have used my own powers to create
the space we now occupy.
124:
But I cannot let the mermaids find
this place—nor can I move it easily. I
used all my reserve powers to help
you.
126:
So I will not hear any bellyaching,
understood? Good.
130:
So wait, what are you doing here?
And why are you avoiding the
mermaids?
134:
Nothing special. Just research. And
I'm not JUST avoiding the mermaids.
I do not want ANYONE to know about
my work.
136:
But never mind that. You're hurt,
correct? Then you should rest. I
won't be sleeping tonight, so the
bed is all yours.
139: And DON'T get any funny ideas.
148:
Is this what you're researching? This
device?
152:
Alk, you are a drifter from another
world, correct?
155:
You show no fear in front of a witch,
nor are you surprised by my
admittedly suspicious research.
158:
Well... Let's just say I have a lot of
friends who defy logic.
161:
No one knows anything about this
strange power of mine. Frankly, it
terrifies me.
165:
That's why I began researching
alchemy, hoping to learn more
about myself... While hiding my
powers from those around me.
168:
When my research saw me
employed by the Gaean Navy, this
device was what I spent my time
working on.
171:
The Navy... Wait, this belongs to the
government?
174: Well, it did. I stole it.
179:
You WHAT?! What were you
thinking?!
183:
You worry too much. All I did was
relieve them of some of their burden.
186:
This device collects data on any
abnormalities in the world.
189:
The activity of the elements, the
sudden surge in drifters and those
with special powers... All of it is
connected. And it signals a change.
192:
And the source of that change is in
the northern sea. While certainly
dangerous, there is no better place
for my research.
196:
Are you sure about that? How about
coming over to my place?
200:
Are you trying to woo me, little boy?
This is neither the time nor place for
such foolishness.
205: Uh, no. That's not what I meant!
207:
...I just thought there might be an
even better place for your research.
210:
And... I think I might have a lead on
the changes you're seeing.
216:
Every star... is another world? But
how could this be? I never—
219: Why would you show this to me?
222:
You understand I am being pursued,
no? I obviously have not revealed
every secret I have to you.
225:
You just... remind me of the others.
We're all trying to figure things out,
and I thought you would want to
know the truth.
227:
That being said, it's not like I'm
forcing you to join us, you know?
232:
You really are an impertinent little
boy.
234: I will do as I see fit.
